Fragrant cherry blossoms dance;
Cool breeze whispers through leaves,
Embracing autumn's golden hue.

As leaves dance to autumn's tune,
Their orange hues embrace the breeze;
Fading echoes of summer's warmth.

Executive Branch: Enforces laws and leads national security efforts;
Judicial Branch: Interprets laws and ensures justice is served;
Legislative Branch: Creates laws, represents constituents, and shares power with the Executive.

O Time, thou art an enigma, an unsolved riddle;
Thou flow'st like water, and yet never ends.
In thy swift passing, we find solace and trouble;
Ever changing seasons, ever-moving bends.

The sunset, it fades, and the dawn comes anew;
With each day, a story unravels and weaves.
Our lives are woven in this intricate tapestry;
Each moment an echo of what has passed or leaves.

In thy grasp, Time, thou holdest our very essence;
The memories that haunt, the dreams that yet elude.
We build upon the past and strive for the present;
Yet always seeking a future we cannot view.

Time, thou art both friend and foe in life's great story;
Forging our destinies with each breath we take.
Though we rush to seize it or slow its passage,
In time, all shall be dust under thy wake.

In the eternal dance of days and nights,
We find ourselves caught in this rhythmic embrace;
The ever-repeating cycle, ever-growing circle,
A reminder of our fleeting place within Time's race.

O Time, thou art a paradox, both ephemeral and enduring;
In thy arms we rest, yet never truly know thy face.
Thus, with each ticking moment, we are forever searching;
For answers to questions that only time can trace.
